      "date": "2019-05-03 14:27:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nBen,\n\nIt would be great to get your review here, since this is sort of a policy change-ish.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "fb2a4c567ca9894bbfb904552961dda5cf35f290",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 797,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "pfarrell",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-05-03 14:34:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nThis seems fine, but the benefit seems small?  If I understand correctly, the jobid will only be referenced during lookup, and if it is found during lookup, then the time will be updated and the time check will save it.\n\nIs there more benefit I missed?\n\nI like adding the warning.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "909b7598b9954bfe569a48da96b1a87aff57eaad",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 428,
        "name": "Wang Shilong",
        "email": "wangshilong1991@gmail.com",
        "username": "wangshilong",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-05-03 14:43:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> This seems fine, but the benefit seems small?  If I understand\n > correctly, the jobid will only be referenced during lookup, and if\n > it is found during lookup, then the time will be updated and the\n > time check will save it.\n > \n > Is there more benefit I missed?\n\nI missed the time update part when I wrote the patch, but patch make a big sense is\nit will avoid newly inserted item removed.\n\nBecause according to current logic, before we updated time and jobid properly, it is init as 0 and\n'\\0' and according to previous reclaim policy, it will be reclaimed if someone come in and trigger\nreclaimer....which is what we have seen this ticket bug have exposed.\n\n > \n > I like adding the warning.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
